Palaeoenvironment. This species is most abundant at localities suggesting silty-sandy inner neritic environments partly with sea grass meadows (e.g. Gainfarn, Steinebrunn) (
Zuschin et al. 2007
) but is also found in pelitic deposits, which might correspond to deeper environments.

Distribution in Central Paratethys.
